RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SULTRY SALLY H pressured the pace through the backstretch, took the nod two deep midway on the turn, dueled clear mid-stretch and widened through later yards. KIMSFAVORITESTORM set a pressured pace inside, was met at the rail midway on the turn, continued close through the upper stretch but flattened the final sixteenth. CLARIFICATION chased, rounded the turn about the five path and ran evenly in the lane. MYSTIC MALIBU ran off in the post parade and was steadied leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the five path and ran evenly in the lane. IRISH ZAPPER chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the four path and passed rivals in an even finish. MARQUET CLASSIC chased outside, raced in the six path of the turn and weakened in the lane. TALENTED CORINNA became fractious in the gate, gave chase toward the inside, raced off the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Kimsfavoritestorm
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,met rail mid turn,flattened 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Talented Corinna
ENTRY.OWNER: Campbell Kim and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious in gate,chased inside,off rail turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Mystic Malibu
ENTRY.COMMENT: ran off post parade,steadied start,chased,5p turn,evenly lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 14100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 4, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Race s Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAPTAIN SAM took the lead past the half mile pole and rated a clear pace inside, came under pressure at the quarter pole, raced near the rail on the turn and was kept alert through the stretch. GARY DOING BIZ chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, eased out leaving the turn and cleared second mid-stretch. MAKE IT A DOUBLE gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn and finished evenly to pass rivals. MARY'S LISTED NEXT chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn and flattened inside the sixteenth pole. SAFE REEZAN gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the four path on the turn then flattened the final sixteenth. NANCYSAIDSO chased outside, raced in the five path of the turn and showed little in the lane. AT THE HALF chased, raced in the three path of the turn and weakened. ADABEL was shuffled back at the start and saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Captain Sam
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated clear pace inside,pressured 1/4,rail turn,kept alert lane

ENTRY.NAME: Make It a Double
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased the pace,rail turn,passed rivals,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Nancysaidso
ENTRY.OWNER: Devane William E and King Adam

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 19100. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, For Each $2,500 To $10,000 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH WARLOCK settled in the three and four paths on the first turn, started a bid approaching the seven sixteenths pole, drew to even terms two deep midway on the far turn and dug in determinedly to inch clear nearing the wire. COLONEL CAPPY took over and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, was met at even terms at the rail midway on the far turn and remained close through the upper stretch, but relented later yards. MR MAJESTIC settled off the rail, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and was steadily handled to just last in third. ONLY GET'N BETTER saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail, eased out leaving the turn, finished evenly and just missed third. BEFRIENDTHEENEMY raced in the two and three paths on the opening turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. DANNY'S WINKSTER stalked inside through the front stretch and raced off the rail on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. ARTHUR S GOLD ducked out leaving the gate, bucked through the opening furlong and was distanced throughout. The Stewards reviewed then dismissed a claim of foul against the rider of Irish Warlock for alleged interference in the stretch, lodged by the rider of Colonel Cappy.

ENTRY.NAME: Danny's Winkster
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside,off rail turn,chased 3/8,faded rail far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Warlock
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace,3& 4p,bid 7/16,even terms mid turn,inched clear late

ENTRY.NAME: Colonel Cappy
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 3/8,met rail mid turn,relented late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIX WHIPS took the lead at the half mile pole and set a pressured pace, widened at the rail on the turn, drifted leaving the turn but was kept sharp through the lane. LEGENDAIRE chased, raced off the rail on the turn, eased out leaving the turn and closed for second later yards. ATLANTIC VAQUERO pressured the pace through the backstretch, dropped back off the rail midway on the turn and flattened inside the eighth pole. SWIFT DANCER pressured the early pace but dropped back past the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn off the rail and weakened in the lane. TALKING TO MYSELF gave chase while saving ground. MONEY MAC chased outside, rounded the turn about the six path and showed little in the lane. FRONT DANCER gave chase but faded in the four path on the turn. IOLA'S BLACK raced well back.

ENTRY.NAME: Swift Dancer
ENTRY.OWNER: Aguilar Jose B and Gallegos Jose M

ENTRY.NAME: Six Whips
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,widened rail near 1/8,drifted,kept sharp

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 20700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MYGIDGETMARIE took over at the rail into the first turn and was firmly rated to show the way, kept the edge over DIAL HER past the three eighths pole and came under pressure leaving the quarter, rounded the far turn at the rail and was steadily handled in the lane. The latter stalked two deep, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. SHES SO SPEIGHTSY rounded the opening turn in the four path, bid leaving the three eighths pole and raced in the five path of the far turn and was along for third late yards. EXTRA CRUNCHY had a brief early lead while tapering inward then stalked into the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path, drifted leaving the turn and flattened in the stretch. MIDNIGHT REGRET was bumped then jostled leaving the gate and saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. LIKELY CHOICE exchanged contact with Midnight Regret leaving the gate then saved ground, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and weakened in the stretch. BIZZY GAL broke awkwardly and made contact with Midnight Regret, raced off the rail on the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. SWEET SPIN was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Mygidgetmarie
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,given rein 3/8,pressured 1/4,steady urging lane

ENTRY.NAME: Likely Choice
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 14400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOWE PATROL was hustled to the lead approaching the three eighths pole and rated the early pace, came under pressure toward the five sixteenths, raced at the rail on the far turn, drew off under steady handling but was taken in hand nearing the wire. S S CASINO GIRL had a brief early lead then gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced close off the rail on the turn, eased out leaving the turn and had to settle for second. SHOWTHEMONEYHONEY chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, was eased to the five path approaching the top of the lane and ran evenly to late stretch before flattening stride. BELIEVE I CAN was jostled at the break and gave early chase outside, rounded the turn near the rail and passed rivals in the lane. IMINCHARGENOW exchanged contact with Believe I Can leaving the gate then engaged in close chase outside, factored from the three path on the turn but was carried out into the lane and flattened stride. PRETTY CASTLE chased, rounded the turn in the five and six paths and ran evenly in the lane. SWISS HORIZON gave close early chase, raced off the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane. GATTOLOTTASPARKLE gave chase then weakened off the rail on the turn. SWEETSTREETDREAMS exchanged contact with Believe I Can leaving the gate and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Iminchargenow
ENTRY.OWNER: Ali Andrew and Schottroffe Edward T
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,chased outside,3p turn,carried out 1/8,evenly lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since March 4 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considere d In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELLIES LIL CASTLE set a pressured pace at mostly even terms with Kilbrittain's Red, raced two deep on the turn and dug in determinedly to edge clear of that one past the sixteenth pole. TIMETOGETUP chased through the backstretch, raced in the four path of the turn and finished evenly to take second late yards. KILBRITTAIN'S RED pressured the winner at mostly even terms, contested the rail on the turn then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. HESSICA chased the leaders through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, eased out leaving the turn and finished well. RUNNING FREE chased toward the inside, rounded the turn off the rail and flattened leaving the eighth pole. SPENCERIAN was bumped at the break then steadied early, picked up the chase outside, rounded the turn about the five path and ran evenly in the lane. GAVINERA pressured the pace inside but dropped back at the rail midway on the turn and weakened in the lane. COUSIN WINNIE chased and flattened in the three path of the turn. AMERICAN BOUND bobbled and made contact with Spencerian leaving the gate, gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane`.

ENTRY.NAME: Gavinera
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace inside,dropped back rail mid turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Spencerian
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,steadied early,chased outside,5p turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Ellies Lil Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,determined lane,edge clear past 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SLOE GIN BIZ settled in the three path the first turn then stalked into the backstretch, started a bid toward the three eighths pole, took the lead three wide approaching the quarter, drew clear midway on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane. TRIPLE TITOS was shuffled back at the start and saved ground on the opening turn, eased out into the backstretch, bid toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path then dueled through the stretch for second. CHERRYS CROSS rated close two deep into the first turn then took the nod past the nine sixteenths pole, came under pressure toward the seven sixteenths, was met approaching the quarter, dropped back off the rail midway on the far turn and relented in the stretch duel for second. BUBBA G ducked out and made contact with SCOOTSCOOT leaving the gate then set the early pace inside, was met past the nine sixteenths pole and gave chase from that point, but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and weakened leaving the turn. The latter was bumped then pinched back leaving the gate, rated close inside on the first turn, raced hemmed in toward the half mile pole, recovered stride approaching the seven sixteenths, rounded the far turn in the three and four paths but weakened leaving the turn. ANGELUS DIAMOND was bumped off stride at the start, settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole but flattened at the rail on the far turn. VIVE BIEN rounded the opening turn about the four path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn but left the turn outside. ROCKY DICE came outward leaving the gate and raced well back. BET ON BITZ hopped from the gate and raced well back in the four path on the opening turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Bubba G
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: ducked out,bumped break,early lead inside,met 9/16,weakened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Scootscoot
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped,pinched start,rated close,hemmed in near 1/2,3& 4p turn

ENTRY.NAME: Triple Titos
ENTRY.COMMENT: shuffled back start,saved ground,bid 7/16,4p far turn,dueled 2nd
